1) WAP to demonstrate process synchronization using wait() system call, where the parent waits for the child process to continue.
A- import os
pid = os.fork()
if pid == 0:
    print("Child process running, PID:", os.getpid())
else: 
    os.wait()
    print("Parent process resumes after child completes, PID:", os.getpid())

O/P:
Child process running, PID: 1234
Parent process resumes after child completes, PID: 1233
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) WAP to create an orphan process, where the parent process terminates before the child process (use sleep()).
A- import os
import time
pid = os.fork()
if pid == 0:
    time.sleep(5)
    print("Child process, PID:", os.getpid())
    print("Parent PID:", os.getppid())
else:
    print("Parent exiting, PID:", os.getpid())

O/P:
Parent exiting, PID: 1233
Child process, PID: 1234
Parent PID: 1
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) WAP to create a zombie process, where the child process terminates but the parent does not wait.
A- import os
import time
pid = os.fork()
if pid == 0:
    print("Child exiting, PID:", os.getpid())
    os._exit(0)
else:
    time.sleep(10)
    print("Parent running, PID:", os.getpid())

O/P:
Child exiting, PID: 1234
Child becomes zombie for some time
Parent running, PID: 1233
